article.headline: Ark.-Pine Bluff 52, Alabama A&M 45
article.story: PINE BLUFF, Ark. (AP) -- George Davis had 16 points and nine rebounds to lead Arkansas-Pine Bluff over Alabama A&M 52-45 Monday night. Jason Frierson and Larry Williams added 13 points each for the Golden Lions (3-11, 1-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who overcame a sloppy performance in which they had 18 turnovers and only seven assists. Cornelius Hester scored 10 points for Alabama A&M (5-10, 0-4). William Byrd was held to only four points for UAPB on 2-of-12 shooting. He also had eight turnovers. Alabama A&M shot 3-of-23 from 3-point range. UAPB was 6-of-19 -- Frierson and Williams made three apiece.
